  <statement>
      <p>
          A sociologist wants to know what proportion of a town's residents feel like they trust their neighbors.  They want to find a <m> 95</m>% confidence interval with margin of error <m>ME=0.03</m>.
      </p>
      <p>
          A previous study showed that  of <m>72\ </m> surveyed residents ,  <m>56\ </m>trusted their neighbors.  How many residents should the sociologist survey now to obtain a <m>95</m>% confidence interval with margin of error <m>ME=0.03</m>?
      </p>
      
