  <answer>
      <title>Partial Solution:</title>
      <ul>
          <li>
              The sample proportion of the initial study is <m>\hat{p}=0.7777777777777778</m>.
          </li>
          <li>
              For a 95% confidence interval,  <m>z^*=1.9599639845400536</m>.
          </li>
          <li>
              The margin of error is <m>ME=0.03</m>.
          </li>
          <li>
              The number of residents should the sociologist survey now is at least <m>738</m>.
          </li>
      </ul>
          
      
